<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-09-08T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-09-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="294" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d294">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">Paris Peace Conf. 181.9202/91:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Commission to Negotiate
                                    Peace</gloss> to Officer in Charge in General <persName type="to">Bandholtz</persName>’ Absence</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-09-08">September 8, 1919</date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>27. [From Polk.] Please rush following message to General Bandholtz: “Do
                            not be drawn into discussion of diplomatic questions with Roumanian
                            officials. Please telegraph immediately object of your trip.” Polk.</p>
                        <closer><hi rend="smallcaps">Am</hi>[<hi rend="smallcaps">erican</hi>] <hi rend="smallcaps">Mission</hi></closer>
                    </div>
